Avoid wars you can't win,

36
00:04:02,410 --> 00:04:06,070
更不要为奴隶制这样愚蠢的原因而战
and never raise your flag for a asinine cause like slavery.

37
00:04:06,280 --> 00:04:07,630
-他就来  -好
- He's on his way. - Fine.

38
00:04:13,400 --> 00:04:14,670
人们会忘记这事的
People will move on.

39
00:04:15,280 --> 00:04:17,200
不会的  你说的越少  他们越会去挖掘
They won't. The less you say, the more they'll dig.

40
00:04:17,210 --> 00:04:18,040
那就让他们挖
Let them.

41
00:04:19,100 --> 00:04:20,640
薇拉  能让我们单独待会儿吗
Willa, could you give us two seconds?

42
00:04:22,460 --> 00:04:23,660
我就在外面
I'll be right outside.

43
00:04:31,720 --> 00:04:34,070
麦金尼斯的事发生在大学时期
McGinnis happened in college.

44
00:04:34,350 --> 00:04:36,000
堕胎则是五年之后的事
The abortion happened five years later.

45
00:04:37,580 --> 00:04:39,470
没有留下任何病历
There aren't any medical records.

46
00:04:39,480 --> 00:04:40,290
完全没有吗
None at all?

47
00:04:41,300 --> 00:04:42,730
我们特别确保了这一点
We specifically made sure.

48
00:04:43,940 --> 00:04:45,440
护士呢  等候室的人呢
A nurse? Somebody in the waiting room?

49
00:04:45,440 --> 00:04:46,960
只有医生一个人在场
The doctor was the only one there.

50
00:04:46,960 --> 00:04:47,960
那他现在在哪里
Then where is he now?

51
00:04:48,100 --> 00:04:50,480
已经是很久以前的事了  康纳  他去世了
It's a long time ago, Connor. He passed away.

52
00:04:50,490 --> 00:04:53,580
如果我都不担心  那你也不必
And if I'm not worried, you shouldn't be.

53
00:04:54,370 --> 00:04:58,190
就算如此  性侵的事现在成为焦点了
Even still, sexual assault is part of the conversation now.

54
00:04:58,700 --> 00:05:00,670
所有的文章和专栏都会提到你
Every article and column mentions you.

55
00:05:00,670 --> 00:05:03,570
如果我们不提供素材  就无法塑造你的形象
If we offer nothing, we can't shape your image.

56
00:05:03,620 --> 00:05:05,890
我说的很清楚  我不想曝光
I made it very clear I don't want exposure.

57
00:05:06,040 --> 00:05:08,450
等我们有新东西可说的时候  我们再说
When we have something new to say, we'll say it.

58
00:05:10,760 --> 00:05:13,710
薇拉  参谋长联席会议那边怎么样了
Willa. Any luck with the Joint Chiefs?

59
00:05:13,840 --> 00:05:15,990
主席办公室还是说他没空
The Chairman's Office still says he's unavailable.

60
00:05:15,990 --> 00:05:19,440
但他们说可以派参谋部主任过来
But they did offer to send the Director of the Joint Staff,

61
00:05:20,590 --> 00:05:21,630
明天上午11点
11:00 a.m. tomorrow.

62
00:05:21,670 --> 00:05:22,480
定下来
Confirm it.

63
00:05:22,850 --> 00:05:24,930
我们去白宫西楼弗兰西斯的办公室见  
We'll meet in Francis' office at the West Wing.

64
00:05:24,940 --> 00:05:25,630
还有别的事吗
Anything else?

65
00:05:25,690 --> 00:05:27,990
没了  我该出发了
No. I should get going, hit the road.

66
00:05:27,990 --> 00:05:28,940
谢谢你  康纳
Thank you, Connor.

67
00:05:30,610 --> 00:05:32,570
接通布鲁克斯议员女士的电话
Get Congresswoman Brooks on the phone.

68
00:05:33,530 --> 00:05:36,020
看看第一夫人今天下午是否有空
And see if the First Lady will be available this afternoon.

69
00:05:38,070 --> 00:05:40,430
你想要给中国所有参加峰会的人做简报吗
You want a brief on everyone on the Chinese side of the Summit?

70
00:05:40,430 --> 00:05:43,410
不  杜兰特在华盛顿做的只是表面功夫
No. What Durant's doing in Washington is just the facade.

71
00:05:43,410 --> 00:05:45,160
这可是真正的谈判
This is the real negotiation.

72
00:05:45,280 --> 00:05:46,710
把你手上关于冯的资料都给我
Give me what you have on Feng.

73
00:05:47,890 --> 00:05:51,560
冯山德  家族在共产党内很有影响
Xander Feng. Deep family connections to the Party.

74
00:05:51,560 --> 00:05:53,570
他祖父曾跟毛泽东肩并肩作战
Grandfather fought side by side with Mao.

75
00:05:53,960 --> 00:05:55,370
在电信业势力很大
Big in the telecom industry.

76
00:05:55,370 --> 00:05:57,670
净资产估计有五百亿
Estimated net worth is over 50 billion.

77
00:05:58,010 --> 00:05:59,230
比雷蒙德还有钱
More than Raymond's.

78
00:05:59,540 --> 00:06:01,120
多几十亿  但谁在乎呢
By a few billion. But who's counting?

79
00:06:02,220 --> 00:06:03,790
除了稀土金属精炼厂之外
Do they have any other business partnerships

80
00:06:03,790 --> 00:06:05,840
他们还有其他商业合作吗
other than the Rare Earth Refinery?

81
00:06:05,880 --> 00:06:06,880
我没有发现
Not that I could find.

82
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:08,950
好吧  向杜兰特询问一下进度
All right. Get a progress update from Durant.

83
00:06:08,950 --> 00:06:11,630
告诉她我们一得知冯的要求就通知她
Tell her I'll be in touch as soon as we know what Feng wants.

84
00:06:13,600 --> 00:06:16,360
雷蒙德·塔斯克这样的人涉足外交事务
When a man like Raymond Tusk gets involved in state diplomacy,

85
00:06:16,360 --> 00:06:18,810
绝不是为了获得诺贝尔和平奖
you can be sure he's not after the Nobel Peace Prize.

86
00:06:18,970 --> 00:06:21,400
他是个机会主义者  但我也是
He's an opportunist. But so am I.

87
00:06:22,280 --> 00:06:25,470
也许这是我的机会  能让他放松对总统的控制
Maybe this is my opportunity to loosen his grip on the President.

88
00:06:26,890 --> 00:06:29,380
副总统先生  你什么时候回华盛顿
Mr. Vice President, when are you returning to Washington?

89
00:06:29,390 --> 00:06:30,960
-副总统先生  你是否...  -副总统先生
- Mr. Vice President, are you... - Mr. Vice President,

90
00:06:30,960 --> 00:06:32,560
你会在斯波特瑟尔韦尼亚待多久
do you have any idea how long you'll be in Spotsylvania?

91
00:06:32,560 --> 00:06:34,570
对于跟中国的谈判有什么看法吗
Any comments on the talks with the Chinese?

92
00:06:34,570 --> 00:06:36,390
能否就即将到来的峰会谈判发表一下看法
Can we get a comment on the upcoming Summit talks?

93
00:06:36,390 --> 00:06:37,140
副总统今天
Vice President will be working

94
00:06:37,150 --> 00:06:39,000
将在自己的房间里办公
from his room for the remainder of the day.

95
00:06:39,300 --> 00:06:39,800
有消息再通知你们
We'll let you know.

96
00:06:39,800 --> 00:06:42,110
先生  你什么时候回华盛顿
Sir, when are you returning to Washington?

97
00:06:54,390 --> 00:06:57,470
冯先生  很高兴见到你
Mr. Feng. It's a pleasure.

98
00:06:57,730 --> 00:06:59,500
彼此彼此  副总统先生
Likewise, Mr. Vice President.

99
00:07:02,380 --> 00:07:03,550
喝咖啡还是喝茶
Coffee? Tea?

100
00:07:03,550 --> 00:07:05,360
有人问过了  谢谢
I've already been offered, but thank you.

101
00:07:05,450 --> 00:07:06,350
谢谢你  密查姆
Thank you, Meechum.

102
00:07:11,030 --> 00:07:12,670
从北京飞过来时间很长
It's a long flight from Beijing.

103
00:07:12,670 --> 00:07:14,190
你一定累坏了
You must be exhausted.

104
00:07:14,380 --> 00:07:16,020
我一直按西方时间作息
I keep Western hours.

105
00:07:16,050 --> 00:07:17,600
和你们没有时差
My midnight is your midnight.

106
00:07:18,820 --> 00:07:21,950
你已经看过计划书了吗
So, have you had a chance to look over the proposal?

107
00:07:21,950 --> 00:07:22,710
看了
I have.

108
00:07:22,920 --> 00:07:23,710
我们开始吧
Shall we?

109
00:07:24,220 --> 00:07:25,030
第四页
Page four.

110
00:07:28,360 --> 00:07:29,560
精炼厂
The refinery.

111
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:31,370
与塔斯克先生合作
With Mr. Tusk.

112
00:07:31,950 --> 00:07:33,320
与竞标价最高的人合作
With the highest bidder.

113
00:07:35,270 --> 00:07:36,930
我们准备与克雷顿-维斯特签订一份
We're prepared to offer Clayton West

114
00:07:36,930 --> 00:07:40,240
梅梅稀土金属精炼厂的40年租约
a 40-year lease on the Mei Mei Rare Earth Elements Refinery.

115
00:07:40,650 --> 00:07:42,110
租约上会有我的名字
To which I will lend my name.

116
00:07:42,900 --> 00:07:45,470
我知道你和雷蒙德是生意伙伴
I understand that you and Raymond are business associates,

117
00:07:45,470 --> 00:07:47,490
但你还是得公开招标
but you're gonna have to open it up to bidding.

118
00:07:47,850 --> 00:07:49,930
塔斯克先生出价肯定比其他人高
Mr. Tusk will outbid any competitors.

119
00:07:49,930 --> 00:07:53,320
尽管如此  过场还是得走
Well, even so, you know, for appearances.

120
00:07:53,600 --> 00:07:56,680
好吧  过场  如果你坚持
Yes. Appearances. If you must.

121
00:07:57,460 --> 00:07:59,580
那这里就没问题了
So, there are no issues here, then?

122
00:07:59,670 --> 00:08:00,840
我们继续吧
We may proceed.

123
00:08:01,270 --> 00:08:02,280
第六页
Page six.

124
00:08:04,300 --> 00:08:05,120
大桥
The bridge.

125
00:08:06,330 --> 00:08:08,230
财政部外资投资管理委员会将批准
The Committee on Foreign Investment will approve

126
00:08:08,230 --> 00:08:10,120
一项基础建设示范工程
a pilot infrastructure project

127
00:08:10,120 --> 00:08:12,570
建设一座从杰斐逊港到米尔福德市
to build a bridge over the Long Island Sound,

128
00:08:12,570 --> 00:08:14,320
横跨长岛海峡的大桥
from Port Jefferson to Milford,

129
00:08:14,450 --> 00:08:17,380
以25年的过桥收费权作为交换
in exchange for a 25-year toll-taking contract.

130
00:08:18,430 --> 00:08:19,940
在我们考虑大桥前
Before we consider the bridge,

131
00:08:19,940 --> 00:08:21,820
我想先讨论另一件事
there's one more item I'd like to discuss.

132
00:08:22,190 --> 00:08:24,190
"考虑"  我以为大桥的事已经定了
"Consider"? I thought the bridge was definite.

133
00:08:24,350 --> 00:08:25,550
没什么是确定的
Nothing is definite.

134
00:08:25,550 --> 00:08:28,630
这座大桥是首要任务
This bridge is a priority-one item.

135
00:08:28,630 --> 00:08:31,430
对你们总统非常重要  我明白
It's very important to your President. I understand.

136
00:08:33,070 --> 00:08:34,520
你想讨论什么
What would you like to discuss?

137
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:36,580
你们在世界贸易组织
The currency manipulation suit which

138
00:08:36,580 --> 00:08:39,000
指控我们进行汇率操纵
you have filed against us in the World Trade Organization.

139
00:08:40,120 --> 00:08:42,040
我们已经同意
Which we are prepared to drop

140
00:08:42,350 --> 00:08:44,150
如果满足其他条件就撤销指控
if all other conditions are met.

141
00:08:44,730 --> 00:08:46,270
我们这次会面就是为了讨论
The point of this meeting is to allow us

142
00:08:46,270 --> 00:08:48,900
不适合在正式场合谈论的事  对吗
to say things that cannot be said in formal settings, yes?

143
00:08:49,210 --> 00:08:50,650
是的  当然
Yes. Of course.

144
00:08:51,220 --> 00:08:52,980
我们不希望你们撤诉
We don't want you to drop the lawsuit.

145
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:55,150
抱歉  我
Forgive me. I...

146
00:08:56,910 --> 00:08:58,010
我不明白
I don't understand.

147
00:08:58,010 --> 00:08:59,960
别在世贸组织让步
Do not back off in the WTO.

148
00:09:01,890 --> 00:09:03,310
但你们在汇率操纵上
But you've been fighting us

149
00:09:03,310 --> 00:09:05,040
已经和我们斗争多年了
on currency manipulation for years.

150
00:09:05,040 --> 00:09:06,940
自由浮动汇率是大势所趋
A free-floating currency is inevitable.

151
00:09:08,150 --> 00:09:10,080
这下我有下手的空间了
Now I have something I can work with.

152
00:09:11,660 --> 00:09:13,200
为什么突然改变主意
Why the sudden change of heart?

153
00:09:13,430 --> 00:09:17,030
并不突然  只是我们这些有远见的人
Not sudden, it has taken those of us who are more forward-thinking

154
00:09:17,190 --> 00:09:18,990
花了很多年才说服其他同僚
many years to convince our counterparts.

155
00:09:18,990 --> 00:09:20,280
那中国直接执行就得了
But China could just do it.

156
00:09:20,280 --> 00:09:23,580
你我都清楚  你们不需要世贸组织的裁定
I mean, you know as well as I, you don't require a WTO ruling.

157
00:09:23,600 --> 00:09:25,120
就像你说的  得走过场
Appearances, as you say.

158
00:09:25,540 --> 00:09:27,820
一定要看起来像是受美国逼迫
It's important that it looks like America forced us out,

159
00:09:27,820 --> 00:09:28,870
而不是我们主动投降
not that we gave in.

160
00:09:31,700 --> 00:09:33,230
那我需要时间
Well, I'll need a little more time,

161
00:09:33,240 --> 00:09:35,180
去和总统商量
so that I can brief the President.

162
00:09:35,180 --> 00:09:37,370
我会耐心等待
I'm here for as long as necessary.

163
00:09:37,780 --> 00:09:39,300
无论你要找谁商量
However you would like to communicate,

164
00:09:39,380 --> 00:09:40,320
我都不管
I leave that to you.

165
00:09:41,140 --> 00:09:42,400
谢谢  副总统先生
Thank you, Mr. Vice President.

166
00:09:42,400 --> 00:09:43,650
谢谢  冯先生
Thank you, Mr. Feng.

167
00:09:49,360 --> 00:09:52,860
在加夫尼我们有自己的外交特色
In Gaffney we had our own brand of diplomacy:

168
00:09:53,220 --> 00:09:56,650
一边握手言欢  一边做好准备
Shake with your right hand, but hold a rock in your left.

169
00:10:01,010 --> 00:10:02,620
看看是谁困在这儿了
Well, look who got stuck with the pool.

170
00:10:02,620 --> 00:10:05,120
我们来这儿简直是找虐
We volunteered because we hate ourselves.

171
00:10:05,130 --> 00:10:06,570
南方前线一切顺利吧
All's well on the Southern front?

172
00:10:06,600 --> 00:10:08,610
没新闻就是没新闻
No news is no news.

173
00:10:08,620 --> 00:10:10,910
我听说那里还有火枪呢
Come on. I hear there's muskets out there.

174
00:10:10,960 --> 00:10:12,540
你什么时候能给我们点猛料
When you giving us something real?

175
00:10:12,630 --> 00:10:14,520
我们正身处美丽的斯波特瑟尔韦尼亚
We're here in beautiful Spotsylvania, aren't we?

