而不是什么右翼狂热分子  打算摧毁...
That you're not just some right-wing fanatic who wants to destro?

351
00:17:55,750 --> 00:18:00,170
否则我就不会亲自登门拜访了
Because I wouldn't have done you the courtesy of paying a visit.

352
00:18:00,790 --> 00:18:01,950
来的就不是我
There would've been an army of

353
00:18:01,950 --> 00:18:04,730
而是一队卫星转播车了
satellite trucks at your door instead of me.

354
00:18:06,440 --> 00:18:09,610
我不会告诉任何人的  如果你是担心这个
Well, I won't tell anyone, if that's what you're worried about.

355
00:18:10,570 --> 00:18:11,360
我相信您
I believe you.

356
00:18:13,500 --> 00:18:16,930
您丈夫有没有对他帮助过的女人做过任何记录
Did your husband keep records of any kind of who he assisted?

357
00:18:17,160 --> 00:18:20,110
任何东西  笔记或非公开记录
Anything at all? Notes? Unofficial records?

358
00:18:20,420 --> 00:18:21,790
他有一本日记
He kept a journal.

359
00:18:22,210 --> 00:18:23,260
您还能找到吗
Do you still have it?

360
00:18:39,230 --> 00:18:39,950
我能看看吗
May I?

361
00:18:41,120 --> 00:18:41,950
看吧
Go ahead.

362
00:18:46,070 --> 00:18:47,500
我得把它带走
Oh. I need to take this with me.

363
00:18:48,110 --> 00:18:50,290
你不能把那页撕掉吗
Can't you just take out that page?

364
00:18:50,690 --> 00:18:53,410
如果有人找到这本日记  这几页又缺了
Someone finds this with pages missing,

365
00:18:53,410 --> 00:18:54,820
那会引起怀疑
that could raise eyebrows.

366
00:18:55,140 --> 00:18:57,810
这里面有他60年的人生
There's 60 years of his life in there.

367
00:18:58,270 --> 00:19:00,630
从我们相遇到他去世
From when we met until he died.

368
00:19:01,830 --> 00:19:03,490
那您希望那六十年被遗忘
And do you want six decades

369
00:19:03,500 --> 00:19:07,490
却只剩下25年前8月的一个晚上吗
reduced to one night in August...25 years ago?

370
00:19:09,560 --> 00:19:11,590
想象一下这里当时的情形
Now just imagine what it looked like back then.

371
00:19:11,850 --> 00:19:13,490
山脊边缘是茂密的灌木丛
The edge of the ridge was a dense thicket,

372
00:19:13,490 --> 00:19:17,610
北方军队得以长驱直入  在骡子鞋列队
which allowed the Northern troops to come in and form on the Mule Shoe.

373
00:19:17,610 --> 00:19:19,510
南方军在山脊顶端
Now the Southern regiments were entrenched

374
00:19:19,510 --> 00:19:21,490
这一带挖好了战壕
in this area at the apex of the line.

375
00:19:21,970 --> 00:19:22,800
如您所见
As you can see,

376
00:19:22,800 --> 00:19:25,950
这里的地形迫使双方向下走  逼近彼此
the topography really forced the two sides down towards each other.

377
00:19:26,490 --> 00:19:28,000
这里就是血腥角
This is the Bloody Angle.

378
00:19:28,140 --> 00:19:28,860
没错
That's right.

379
00:19:29,150 --> 00:19:30,690
我昨晚还读到了相关内容
I was reading about it last night.

380
00:19:30,700 --> 00:19:32,630
短兵相接  白刃相见
Close quarters, hand-to-hand combat.

381
00:19:33,140 --> 00:19:36,640
据说  南北双方共有一万五千名士兵
All told, about 15,000 Union-Confederate soldiers

382
00:19:36,640 --> 00:19:38,650
在血腥角这块半英里宽的战场上
lost their lives here at the Bloody Angle, on a battlefield

383
00:19:38,650 --> 00:19:40,250
失去了生命
that's only about half a mile wide.

384
00:19:41,880 --> 00:19:44,280
副总统先生  我们今天为您准备了一份惊喜
Now, Mr. Vice President, we have a surprise for you today.

385
00:19:44,670 --> 00:19:48,070
向您介绍麦高文旅第12军团的
I'd like to introduce you to Corporal Augustus Elijah Underwood

386
00:19:48,070 --> 00:19:50,540
奥古斯都·以利亚·安德伍德下士
of the 12th Regiment of the McGowan Brigade,

387
00:19:50,770 --> 00:19:52,640
您的曾曾曾祖父
your great-great-great-grandfather.

388
00:19:53,300 --> 00:19:54,860
我在这场战役中牺牲于此
I died here in this battle.

389
00:19:55,270 --> 00:19:57,010
我觉得是搞错了吧
I think there's been a mistake.

390
00:19:57,010 --> 00:19:59,620
我祖父从没说过祖上有人参加过内战
My grandfather never mentioned any Underwoods in the war.

391
00:19:59,620 --> 00:20:00,340
我们做过调查
We did our research.

392
00:20:00,340 --> 00:20:01,910
他就是在这里战斗牺牲的
He definitely fought and died here.

393
00:20:01,910 --> 00:20:04,210
我只有24岁  而我儿子
I was 24. And my son,

394
00:20:04,210 --> 00:20:06,720
你的曾曾祖父只有两岁
your great-great-grandfather was two years old.

395
00:20:06,910 --> 00:20:07,950
我从没见过他
I never met him.

396
00:20:08,070 --> 00:20:10,620
就是在这里吗  在血腥角
It happened here, at the Bloody Angle?

397
00:20:10,620 --> 00:20:11,740
在那片林子边上
At the edge of those woods.

398
00:20:12,690 --> 00:20:14,340
我的脑袋被石头砸扁了
My skull was bashed in with a rock.

399
00:20:14,340 --> 00:20:15,440
奥古斯都  谢谢你
Augustus, thank you.

400
00:20:15,450 --> 00:20:17,960
这边  还有一些
Now, uh, over here we've got something that's,

401
00:20:17,960 --> 00:20:19,310
有趣的东西
uh, very interesting as well.

402
00:20:19,310 --> 00:20:20,780
等一下
Uh, j—just a moment.

403
00:20:26,690 --> 00:20:27,610
接着说
Tell me more.

404
00:20:28,040 --> 00:20:29,450
当时正是半夜
It was the middle of the night.

405
00:20:30,350 --> 00:20:32,910
我们的子弹打光了  只剩下刺刀
And we were out of musket balls, just bayonets.

406
00:20:32,910 --> 00:20:36,110
而且只有一半人有刺刀  我什么都没有
Only half of us had those. I had nothing.

407
00:20:37,050 --> 00:20:38,330
只能靠这双手
Just these hands.

408
00:20:39,590 --> 00:20:41,880
天很黑  什么都看不见
So dark, couldn't see nothing.

409
00:20:42,560 --> 00:20:44,780
但能听北方佬在朝我们跑来
But you could hear 'em, the Yanks, runnin' toward us.

410
00:20:45,290 --> 00:20:46,700
接着就能闻到他们了
And then you could smell 'em.

411
00:20:47,270 --> 00:20:48,610
我遇到的第一个北方佬
First Yank that brushed up against me,

412
00:20:48,610 --> 00:20:51,050
被我掐住了脖子  倒在地上
I grab him by the throat, fall down on the ground.

413
00:20:52,320 --> 00:20:54,920
我用力打他  打到皮开肉绽
I bit him so hard, I could taste the bone.

414
00:20:57,860 --> 00:20:59,760
然后他抓起一块石头  砸中了这里
Then he grabs a rock and brings it down right here.

415
00:21:00,130 --> 00:21:01,040
我就这么死了
And that was that.

416
00:21:01,790 --> 00:21:04,620
我被埋在万人冢里  没有墓碑
I was buried in a mass grave, no headstone.

417
00:21:05,390 --> 00:21:06,980
能给您和奥古斯都拍张合影吗
Could we get a picture with you and Augustus?

418
00:21:07,760 --> 00:21:08,530
好
Yes.

419
00:21:16,230 --> 00:21:17,050
谢谢你
Thank you.

420
00:21:22,890 --> 00:21:24,580
他相当认真啊
He takes it rather seriously.

421
00:21:24,580 --> 00:21:26,450
是啊  他们都很认真
Oh, yeah. They all do.

422
00:21:27,840 --> 00:21:29,950
前面有我们重建的
Now, up ahead, we have examples of,

423
00:21:29,950 --> 00:21:32,680
邦联军壁垒的模型
uh, Confederate ramparts that we've reconstructed.

424
00:21:32,700 --> 00:21:35,100
可以看到他们是如何伐木挖战壕的
And you can see how they cut the timber and made the trenches.

425
00:21:35,110 --> 00:21:36,350
在战斗过程中
Now these trenches traded hands

426
00:21:36,350 --> 00:21:38,200
这些战壕几次易手
many times over the course of the battle.

427
00:21:42,270 --> 00:21:43,510
你有钥匙
You have keys.

428
00:21:43,740 --> 00:21:45,870
你归我们管  没错  我们有钥匙
We own you. Yes, we have keys.

429
00:21:45,880 --> 00:21:46,800
我去把衣服穿上
I'm gonna put some clothes on.

430
00:21:46,800 --> 00:21:48,140
别想衣服的事了
Forget your clothes.

431
00:21:48,880 --> 00:21:51,360
你的原话"你真想这么做吗"
And I quote, "You sure you wanna do this?"

432
00:21:51,360 --> 00:21:54,300
"我没选择了  但你还有"
And I quote, "I don't have a choice, but you do."

433
00:21:54,820 --> 00:21:56,640
你他妈以为自己在干什么
What the fuck do you think you're doing?

434
00:21:56,680 --> 00:21:58,240
他应该知道他究竟要做什么
He should know what he's getting into.

435
00:22:00,430 --> 00:22:02,010
这是丝绸睡裤吗
Are those silk pajamas?

436
00:22:05,600 --> 00:22:07,450
近距离看更有档次了
Looks even fancier in person.

437
00:22:10,800 --> 00:22:11,580
腰果
Cashew.

438
00:22:14,550 --> 00:22:16,500
不  别碰她
No. Don't touch her.

439
00:22:17,040 --> 00:22:19,210
过来  小家伙
Hey, there, little guy.

440
00:22:24,180 --> 00:22:27,360
我以前在监控里见过你
I've seen you before on camera, hmm?

441
00:22:27,370 --> 00:22:28,680
请把她放下
Please put her down.

442
00:22:34,980 --> 00:22:36,850
不要冒险
Don't take the chance.

443
00:22:38,790 --> 00:22:40,880
这这双鞋是在彭尼百货公司买的
I bought these shoes at J.C. Penney,

444
00:22:40,880 --> 00:22:42,350
含税价72块
$72 with tax.

445
00:22:42,350 --> 00:22:45,250
橡胶鞋底  用水就能冲干净
Rubber soles. You can clean 'em off with a hose.

446
00:22:45,250 --> 00:22:46,220
求求你  你弄伤她了
Please, you're hurting her.

447
00:22:46,960 --> 00:22:50,000
我也有一只宠物  他叫嘉文·奥尔西
I have a pet, too. His name is Gavin Orsay.

448
00:22:51,310 --> 00:22:52,240
坐下
Sit.

449
00:22:56,410 --> 00:22:57,760
我说"坐下"
I said, "Sit."

450
00:23:05,570 --> 00:23:07,700
瞧瞧你多乖呀  嘉文
Look what a good boy you are, Gavin.

451
00:23:16,610 --> 00:23:17,820
你想让我这么做吗
Is that what you need me to do?

452
00:23:17,820 --> 00:23:22,120
安静  我说"去捡"  你就去
Quiet. When I say "fetch," you fetch.

453
00:23:22,660 --> 00:23:26,010
现在我们去抓卢卡斯  就像我们说好的那样
And now we are going to fetch Lucas, just like we discussed.

454
00:23:27,980 --> 00:23:32,790
你要是敢咬我  我就杀了你
If you try to bite my hand, I will put you to sleep.

455
00:23:36,580 --> 00:23:38,120
介意我拿两瓶吗
Mind if I take a couple?

456
00:23:56,760 --> 00:23:59,270
道格·斯坦普  我是副总统的幕僚长
Doug Stamper, I'm the Vice President's Chief of Staff.

457
00:23:59,270 --> 00:24:00,980
我知道  坐吧
I know. Sit down.

458
00:24:03,440 --> 00:24:05,430
我祖父参加过革命
My grandfather fought in the Revolution.

459
00:24:06,530 --> 00:24:07,860
中国当时很穷
China was poor, then.

460
00:24:08,070 --> 00:24:09,410
很难买到糖
Sugar was hard to come by.

461
00:24:10,390 --> 00:24:12,380
现在中国到处能买到糖
Now sugar's everywhere in China.

462
00:24:15,650 --> 00:24:17,160
要来杯古典鸡尾酒吗
Do you like Old-Fashioneds?

463
00:24:17,570 --> 00:24:18,450
不  谢谢
No, thanks.

464
00:24:19,940 --> 00:24:21,100
我看到新闻了
I've seen the news.

465
00:24:21,950 --> 00:24:24,650
你们政府对我们撤诉非常高兴
Your government was enthusiastic about our dropping the suit.

466
00:24:25,030 --> 00:24:27,270
他们还在国内将其鼓吹为一场胜利
They've touted it as a victory back home.

467
00:24:27,270 --> 00:24:30,390
确实是胜利  但不是我们想要的胜利
It is a victory, but not the victory we wanted.

468
00:24:30,750 --> 00:24:32,680
这让我们很难相信
We're finding that difficult to believe.

469
00:24:32,680 --> 00:24:34,490
你说我们  是指副总统吧
By "we," you mean the Vice President.

470
00:24:34,700 --> 00:24:36,180
我指的是美国政府
I mean the American government.

471
00:24:36,180 --> 00:24:38,030
他声称自己就代表美国政府
Which he proclaims to represent.

472
00:24:38,660 --> 00:24:41,170
没错  而我代表他
He does. And I'm representing him.

473
00:24:41,970 --> 00:24:43,930
斯坦普先生  别吹嘘你的地位
Don't inflate your status, Mr. Stamper.

474
00:24:44,200 --> 00:24:45,680
你不过是个跑腿的
You're nothing but an errand boy.

475
00:24:46,770 --> 00:24:48,540
你要对副总统说什么吗
Do you have a message for the Vice President?

476
00:24:49,080 --> 00:24:51,090
如果他代表美国政府
If he represents the American government,

477
00:24:51,520 --> 00:24:53,870
那他为什么没能转达我的要求
then why did he fail to communicate my request?

478
00:24:54,070 --> 00:24:56,260
我们质疑你的合法性  冯先生
We question your legitimacy, Mr. Feng.

479
00:24:56,280 --> 00:24:58,200
你们代表团的做法和言论
Nothing your delegation has done or said has,

480
00:24:58,200 --> 00:25:00,620
都与你的要求背道而驰
in any way, supported your requests.

481
00:25:05,120 --> 00:25:06,060
闻闻
Smell that.

482
00:25:06,960 --> 00:25:08,340
我用了高档珍稀的麦卡伦
I use Macallan Rare and Fine,

483
00:25:08,340 --> 00:25:11,480
1926年产  一瓶四万美金
1926. $40,000 a bottle.

484
00:25:12,840 --> 00:25:14,770
你以前酗酒  是吗
You used to be an alcoholic, correct?

485
00:25:15,020 --> 00:25:18,470
酒瘾是戒不掉的  只能克制
Not "used to be." Still am. A sober one.

486
00:25:20,100 --> 00:25:21,030
你怀念这味道吗
Do you miss it?

487
00:25:23,270 --> 00:25:24,970
那可是五千美元
Five thousand dollars you just spilled.

488
00:25:24,970 --> 00:25:26,210
我会寄张支票给你
I'll send you a check.

489
00:25:27,330 --> 00:25:30,000
我喜欢你  斯坦普先生  即便你只是个跑腿的
I like you, Mr. Stamper, even if you're just an errand boy.

490
00:25:31,400 --> 00:25:32,620
我再问你一次
I'll ask you again.

491
00:25:33,420 --> 00:25:35,460
你要对副总统说什么吗
What is your message for the Vice President?

492
00:25:36,020 --> 00:25:39,700
恢复起诉  否则杰斐逊港大桥项目将取消
There will be no Port Jefferson Bridge unless the lawsuit is reintroduced.

493
00:25:39,910 --> 00:25:43,250
到时  常委会会有人抗议
When you do, there will be those on the Standing Committee who protest,

494
00:25:43,280 --> 00:25:44,470
我会搞定他们
but I'll manage them.

495
00:25:45,370 --> 00:25:46,760
大多数人想要改革
The majority want reform.

496
00:25:49,160 --> 00:25:50,400
我会告诉副总统
I'll tell the Vice President.

497
00:25:51,840 --> 00:25:53,910
斯坦普先生  还有一条
Mr. Stamper, one more message.

498
00:25:54,800 --> 00:25:56,920
请提醒副总统  我们来这里
Please remind the Vice President that we are both here

499
00:25:56,920 --> 00:25:59,460
是应我们共同的朋友塔斯克先生的邀请
at the behest of our mutual friend, Mr. Tusk.

500
00:26:00,590 --> 00:26:04,160
如果副总统不愿意合作  我就直接跳过他
If the Vice President fails to cooperate, I will simply bypass him.

501
00:26:11,100 --> 00:26:12,130
怎么了
Yes?

502
00:26:13,520 --> 00:26:14,390
是道格
It's Doug.

503
00:26:14,650 --> 00:26:15,530
好吧
Fine.

504
00:26:18,930 --> 00:26:20,190
跟冯谈了
Spoke with Feng.

505
00:26:21,960 --> 00:26:23,150
给你的洋葱圈
Here's your onion rings.

506
00:26:24,600 --> 00:26:27,910
你知道朗斯特里特将军就是在这里
Did you know that General Longstreet was shot here,

507
00:26:27,960 --> 00:26:31,270
被他自己人意外误伤害死的
accidentally, by his own men in the dark?

508
00:26:31,270 --> 00:26:32,700
不  我不知道
No...I didn't.

509
00:26:36,540 --> 00:26:38,290
好吧  跟我介绍一下进展吧
All right. Bring me up to date.

510
00:26:38,300 --> 00:26:39,730
跟冯谈得怎么样了
Where are we with Feng?

511
00:26:40,290 --> 00:26:41,990
他要我们恢复诉讼
He wants us to resume the lawsuit.

512
00:26:42,670 --> 00:26:44,620
看来他要坚持立场
So, he's sticking to his guns.

513
00:26:44,630 --> 00:26:47,190
我们不起诉  大桥项目就取消
If we don't reintroduce it, there's no bridge project.

514
00:26:47,240 --> 00:26:49,660
那样总统会很失望
Well, that would greatly upset the President.

515
00:26:50,470 --> 00:26:52,140
要我转达冯的意思吗
Do you want me to deliver Feng's message?

516
00:26:52,400 --> 00:26:54,060
绝对不要
Absolutely not.

517
00:26:55,000 --> 00:26:56,740
我们就要让总统生气
We want the President angry.

518
00:26:57,090 --> 00:26:59,860
不过要想办法不让他怪罪在我身上
The tricky part is making sure he doesn't direct it toward me.

519
00:27:01,670 --> 00:27:02,800
那你要我做什么
So what do you want me to do?

520
00:27:03,570 --> 00:27:04,990
联系凯茜的人
Get a hold of Cathy's people.

521
00:27:05,730 --> 00:27:08,030
决不能提及诉讼
Do not mention the lawsuit at all.

522
00:27:08,240 --> 00:27:10,630
让他们自己提大桥项目
Have them bring up the bridge instead.

523
00:27:10,630 --> 00:27:12,370
看看冯是不是在虚张声势
Let's see if Feng is bluffing.

524
00:27:12,700 --> 00:27:13,350
是  先生
Yes, sir.

525
00:27:16,820 --> 00:27:20,160
得吸取朗斯特里特的教训  他树大招风
We must learn from Longstreet. He rode too high in the saddle.

526
00:27:20,540 --> 00:27:22,120
如果明天有人朝我开枪
If a bullet comes my way tomorrow,

